# barbergo — before go-live

When the user prepares a **public / production release**, proactively run through `docs/pre-launch-checklist.md` and apply these changes (do not enable during MVP demo unless asked):

## Required env changes

- Set `EXPO_PUBLIC_ADMIN_AUTH_REQUIRED=true` in `apps/mobile/.env` (and document in `.env.example`).
- Restart Expo after env changes.

## Required Supabase hardening

- Ensure barber Auth user exists; admin must use `/admin/login`.
- **Revoke MVP anon policies** from `0002_mvp_anon_bookings_access.sql` on `bookings` (anon read/update). Keep customer booking path working (anon insert with `status = pending` from `0001` is enough if RLS is configured correctly).
- Verify authenticated admin can read/update bookings; anon admin access must fail.

## Agent behavior

- Remind the user of this checklist when they say "go live", "production", "launch", or "release".
- Do not set `EXPO_PUBLIC_ADMIN_AUTH_REQUIRED=true` during normal MVP development unless explicitly requested.
